#creating a server

pgAdmin uses PostgrSQL's 'pgpass' mechanism to store passwords 
on linux
~/.pgpass
#Modify password for role postgres:
sudo -u postgres psql postgres
alter user postgres with password 'admin';

#Now connect to pgadmin using username postgres and password postgres

#Now you can create roles & databases using pgAdmin

#After that create a server connection
#just follow the instraction there

https://www.pgadmin.org/docs/dev/connect.html


